<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>File: Zend/Auth/Adapter/DbTable.php
Line: 412</p>

<p>Why do you catch an Exception and throw it with another message? I've spent an hour figuring out why "the supplied parameter (...) failed (...)". When I went deeper, I found out that it is PDOException that holds a message: "permission denied to relation (...)".</p>

<p>I think that exceptions in Zend Framework should be for developers and should provide maximum information about the state of an application.</p>

